      "id": "0c79ee53-6293-53dd-9c3e-a58ae2b7432d",
      "label": "TextSummary_0c79ee53-6293-53dd-9c3e-a58ae2b7432d",
      "type": "TextSummary",
      "properties": {
        "text": "This document is Swarnendu Bhandari’s résumé detailing his education, experience, projects, awards, and technical skills.\n- In 2020 Swarnendu Bhandari completed Class X at Panchthupi T.N. Institution with 84.7%.\n- In 2022 he finished Class XII at Krishnath College School, scoring 93.8%.\n- In March 2024 he placed second runner‑up at the National Science Week hackathon (KodeInKGP, IIT Kharagpur) for a Subject Recommender project.\n- In September 2024 his team achieved a Top 50 finish at the Internal Hackathon for Smart India Hackathon (Technology Student's Gymkhana, IIT Kharagpur) with a healthcare management system.\n- From February to September 2025 Swarnendu developed Dmaid.cloud, an AI‑powered Mermaid diagram editor using Llama 4 and DeepSeek R1.\n- In June‑July 2025 he published Limiter.js, a TypeScript NPM library for request rate limiting that earned over 200 downloads.\n- Also in June‑July 2025 he built Workspace Copilot, an AI workspace manager integrating LLMs, MCP Server, and calendar/email APIs.\n- Starting December 2025 he leads InfuseAI, an AI platform for rapid app creation, serving as Platform Architect and Team Leader.\n- From October 2025 to July 2026 he interned as a Data Science Intern at Fidelity Investments’ Center of Excellence for Artificial Intelligence, building a large‑scale data ingestion pipeline.\n- In January 2026 he received the Best Deep Tech Idea award from the Entrepreneurship Launchpad Programme at IIT Kharagpur for the InfuseAI concept.\n- Since 2027 Swarnendu is pursuing a dual‑degree M.Tech at IIT Kharagpur with a CGPA of 8.18/10, focusing on AI systems, data engineering, and backend architecture.\n- His technical skill set includes TypeScript, Python, Rust, Java, Solidity, Next.js, React, Prisma, Docker, Firebase, LLM APIs, and cloud‑native tools.",
