    {
      "id": "194d54b3-4db1-5ab6-be6d-7440e6e1e111",
      "label": "DocumentChunk_194d54b3-4db1-5ab6-be6d-7440e6e1e111",
      "type": "DocumentChunk",
      "properties": {
        "text": "# Knowledge Base Document: Swarnendu Resume CZ.pdf\nKnowledge Base ID: 53032dc48ed8417098b3\n\nYear \tDegree \tInstitute\nSWARNENDU BHANDARI\n+91 81101199607 \tswarnendu317@gmail.com \tswarnendu_ \tGitHub \tKharagpur, WB, IN\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nDual Degree student at IIT Kharagpur with strong experience in AI systems, data engineering, and scalable backend architectures.\nProven track record of building production-ready platforms using LLMs, RAG pipelines, and cloud-native designs, including leading\naward-winning deep-tech projects. Hands-on industry exposure through a Data Science internship at Fidelity Investments, delivering\nrobust data pipelines and performance-optimised systems. Adept at system design, developer tooling, and translating complex technical\nideas into real-world impact.\nEDUCATIONS\nCGPA/MARKS\n2027 - Present \tM.TECH Dual Degree \tIIT Kharagpur \t8.18 / 10\n2022 - 2022 \tCLASS XII BOARD EXAM \tKrishnath College School \t93.8%\n2020 - 2020 \tCLASS X BOARD EXAM \tPanchthupi T.N. Institution \t84.7%\nWORK EXPERIENCES\n|\n:\nData Science Intern Internship\nFidelity Investments | Center of Excellence for Artificial Intelligence\nOct 2025 - Jul 2026\nBengaluru, KA\nBuilt a data ingestion pipeline that processed large daily logs and generated summary reports for business stakeholders.\nImplemented background jobs and idempotent processing to handle retries safely and reduce duplicate records.\nImproved end-to-end processing time by optimizing queries and batching writes; added monitoring for failures and latency.\nDocumented the system and created runbooks to help the team support on-call issues.\nTechnologies / Skills Used LLMs, RAG, MCP Server\nPROJECTS\n|\n:\nInfuseAI | AI Platform for Creating AI Apps under 10 minutes \tWebsite Github\nGroup Project | Role: Platform Architect & Team Leader\nDec 2025 - Present\nLed ideation and framing for a production-ready AI platform enabling rapid deployment of knowledge-grounded applications.\nDesigned and architected a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline, optimized for accuracy, latency, and workloads.\nImplemented cloud-native RAG architecture, encompassing data ingestion, vector indexing, retrieval, and LLM orchestration.\nDeveloped a developer SDK for seamless integration of AI assistants into external applications with minimal setup.\nDefined system architecture and API contracts, ensuring modularity, extensibility, and multi-tenant support.\nAuthored comprehensive technical documentation on architecture, SDK usage, deployment workflows, and best practices.\nTechnologies / Tools Used RAG, LLMs, SDK Development, Pinecone\n|\n:\nDmaid.cloud | AI Powered Mermaid Diagram Editor \tWebsite Github\nSelf Project\nFeb 2025 - Sep 2025\nDeveloped an AI-powered, canvas-based Mermaid diagram editor supporting interactive creation of 20+ types of diagrams.\nIntegrated Llama 4 and DeepSeek R1 LLMs for AI-driven Mermaid diagram generation using context-aware prompting.\nEnabled direct embedding of Mermaid diagrams into 3 formats (SVG, HTML and Markdown) through the frontend interface.\nProgrammed undo/redo functionality using stack data structures, supporting up to 300 states through state management.\nIntegrated Google Sign-In authentication using Firebase, enabling secure user onboarding and access control for 50+ users.\nChosen from over 200+ project ideas to present at GradCapital; earned strong feedback and investment interest from the VC.\nTechnologies / Tools Used Mermaid, LLMs, Codemirror\n|\n:\nLimiter.js | NPM Library for Request Rate Limiting \tNpm Github\nSelf Project\nJun 2025 - Jul 2025\nPublished a production-ready TypeScript library Limiter.js; achieved 200+ downloads on NPM.\nImplemented core IPTracker and RateLimiter classes with encapsulated internal state and well-defined public getters and setters.\nArchitected a Detector class with configurable thresholds for adaptive IP rate limiting, temporary bans, and blacklist enforcement.\nDeveloped lightweight middleware modules for backend integration, ensuring minimal configuration and low-latency performance.\nTechnologies / Tools Used Package Development, System Designing, Rate Limiting\n\n-- 1 of 2 --\n\n:\n:\n:\nPROJECTS\n:\nWorkspace Copilot | AI Workspace Manager with Integrated MCP Servers\nSelf Project\nJun 2025 - Jul 2025\nDeveloped a personalized Workspace Copilot integrating Llama 4 with Model Context Protocol, enabling contextual automation.\nEngineered MCP server integrating time, date, calendar, and email with 10+ tools to support modular event scheduling workflows.\nBuilt end-to-end calendar and inbox integration using Calendar and Email APIs, ensuring real-time synchronization across services.\nAutomated event creation, retrieval, and inbox parsing with LLM-driven agents, streamlining user interactions via natural language.\nTechnologies / Tools Used LLMs, MCP Server, Calendar APIs, Email APIs\nAWARDS & ACHIEVEMENTS\nBest Deep Tech Idea | Entrepreneurship Launchpad Programme\nRajendra Mishra School of Engineering Entrepreneurship, IIT Kharagpur\nJan 2026\nPresented the deep-tech startup concept Infuse AI to investors, industry experts, and RMSOEE faculty during final pitch sessions.\nAwarded 'Best Deep Tech Idea' by the Head of School and Vivek Wadhwa (CEO, Vionix Biosciences) for technical depth.\nLed a four-member team, driving ideation, development, pitch strategy, and investor communication throughout the programme.\nSecond runner-up | National Science Week hackathon\nKodeInKGP, IIT Kharagpur\nMar 2024\nSecured 3rd position among 120+ participants at National Science Week Hackathon, organised by KodeInKGP, IIT Kharagpur.\nBuilt a Subject Recommender; led frontend development, and implemented secure authentication protocols using Firebase.\nEngineered the overall system architecture, ensuring modularity, maintainability, and integration of frontend and backend.\nTop 50 | Internal Hackathon for Smart India Hackathon\nTechnology Student's Gymkhana, IIT Kharagpur\nSep 2024\nDeveloped core functional modules including patient intake, doctor scheduling, inventory tracking, and billing management.\nAchieved Top 50 position competing against 195 teams and 1170+ participants, with strong technical and leadership capabilities.\nSKILLS\nProgramming Languages \tTypescript, Python, C, Rust, Java, Javascript, Solidity\nFrameworks & Libraries \tNext.js, React.js, Prisma, Numpy, Pandas, Express.js, OpenAPI Spec, Mongoose, Socket.io\nTools & Platforms \tGit, GitHub, Docker, Bash, Postman, Linux, Firebase, Google Gemini APIs, Cloudflare,\nMongoDB Atlas, LLM APIs\nCOURSEWORK INFORMATION\nComputer Science: Programming and Data Structures, Object Oriented Programming, Low Level Design (LLD), React, GraphQL\nMathematics: Advanced Calculus, Linear Algebra, Probability and Statistics, Reliability Engineering, Geoinformatics\n\n-- 2 of 2 --",
